The Human Settlements has approved R16 million towards rebuilding of the destroyed housing structures at the Alfred Nzo District Municipality which was destroyed by recent floods. eNCA speaks to Eastern Cape Human Settlements MEC, Nonceba Kontsiwe. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Human Settlements has approved R16-million for the rebuilding of the destroyed housing structures at the Alfred Nzo District Municipality. The structures were destroyed by recent floods in the province. READ: Eastern Cape floods | Residents' anger spills over In April, a Joint Ministerial task team visited the Eastern Cape to assess the impact of floods on infrastructure. The Eastern Cape is one of the provinces that has been affected by disasters including KwaZulu-Natal and the North West. 